2905 }
2906
2907 for (auto & tag_Re : _sub_Re)
2908 tag_Re[ivn].resize(dof_indices.size() * icount);
2909}

3204
3205void
3206Assembly::processLocalResidual(DenseVector<Number> & res_block,
3207 std::vector<dof_id_type> & dof_indices,
3208 const std::vector<Real> & scaling_factor,
3209 bool is_nodal)
3210{
3211 // For an array variable, ndof is the number of dofs of the zero-th component and
3212 // ntdof is the number of dofs of all components.
3213 // For standard or vector variables, ndof will be the same as ntdof.
3214 auto ndof = dof_indices.size();
3215 auto ntdof = res_block.size();
3216 auto count = ntdof / ndof;
3217 mooseAssert(count == scaling_factor.size(), "Inconsistent of number of components");
3218 mooseAssert(count * ndof == ntdof, "Inconsistent of number of components");
3219 if (count > 1)
3220 {
3221 // expanding dof indices
3222 dof_indices.resize(ntdof);
3223 unsigned int p = 0;
3224 for (MooseIndex(count) j = 0; j < count; ++j)
3225 for (MooseIndex(ndof) i = 0; i < ndof; ++i)
3226 {
3227 dof_indices[p] = dof_indices[i] + (is_nodal ? j : j * ndof);
3228 res_block(p) *= scaling_factor[j];
3229 ++p;
3230 }
3231 }
3232 else
3233 {
3234 if (scaling_factor[0] != 1.0)
3235 res_block *= scaling_factor[0];
3236 }
3237
3238 _dof_map.constrain_element_vector(res_block, dof_indices, false);
3239}
3240
3241void
3242Assembly::addResidualBlock(NumericVector<Number> & residual,
3243 DenseVector<Number> & res_block,
3244 const std::vector<dof_id_type> & dof_indices,
3245 const std::vector<Real> & scaling_factor,
3246 bool is_nodal)
3247{
3248 if (dof_indices.size() > 0 && res_block.size())
3249 {
3250 _temp_dof_indices = dof_indices;
3251 _tmp_Re = res_block;
3252 processLocalResidual(_tmp_Re, _temp_dof_indices, scaling_factor, is_nodal);
3253 residual.add_vector(_tmp_Re, _temp_dof_indices);
3254 }
3255}
3256
3257void
3258Assembly::cacheResidualBlock(std::vector<Real> & cached_residual_values,
3259 std::vector<dof_id_type> & cached_residual_rows,
3260 DenseVector<Number> & res_block,
3261 const std::vector<dof_id_type> & dof_indices,
3262 const std::vector<Real> & scaling_factor,
3263 bool is_nodal)
3264{
3265 if (dof_indices.size() > 0 && res_block.size())
3266 {
3267 _temp_dof_indices = dof_indices;
3268 _tmp_Re = res_block;
3269 processLocalResidual(_tmp_Re, _temp_dof_indices, scaling_factor, is_nodal);
3270
3271 for (MooseIndex(_tmp_Re) i = 0; i < _tmp_Re.size(); i++)
3272 {
3273 cached_residual_values.push_back(_tmp_Re(i));
3274 cached_residual_rows.push_back(_temp_dof_indices[i]);
3275 }
3276 }
3277
3278 res_block.zero();
3279}
3280
3281void
3282Assembly::setResidualBlock(NumericVector<Number> & residual,
3283 DenseVector<Number> & res_block,
3284 const std::vector<dof_id_type> & dof_indices,
3285 const std::vector<Real> & scaling_factor,
3286 bool is_nodal)
3287{
3288 if (dof_indices.size() > 0)

3291 _tmp_Re = res_block;

3499// private method, so no key required
3500void
3501Assembly::clearCachedResiduals(const VectorTag & vector_tag)
3502{
3503 auto & values = _cached_residual_values[vector_tag._type_id];
3504 auto & rows = _cached_residual_rows[vector_tag._type_id];
3505
3506 mooseAssert(values.size() == rows.size(),
3507 "Number of cached residuals and number of rows must match!");
3508
3509 // Keep track of the largest size so we can use it to reserve and avoid
3510 // as much dynamic allocation as possible
3511 if (_max_cached_residuals < values.size())
3512 _max_cached_residuals = values.size();
3513
3514 // Clear both vectors (keeps the capacity the same)
3515 values.clear();
3516 rows.clear();
3517 // And then reserve: use 2 as a fudge factor to *really* avoid dynamic allocation!
3518 values.reserve(_max_cached_residuals * 2);
3519 rows.reserve(_max_cached_residuals * 2);
3520}

3522void
3523Assembly::addCachedResidualDirectly(NumericVector<Number> & residual,
3524 GlobalDataKey,
3525 const VectorTag & vector_tag)
3526{

3528 const auto & rows = _cached_residual_rows[vector_tag._type_id];
3529
3530 mooseAssert(values.size() == rows.size(),
3531 "Number of cached residuals and number of rows must match!");
3532
3533 if (!values.empty())
3534 {
3535 residual.add_vector(values, rows);
3536 clearCachedResiduals(vector_tag);
3537 }

3568// private method, so no key required
3569void
3570Assembly::addJacobianBlock(SparseMatrix<Number> & jacobian,
3571 DenseMatrix<Number> & jac_block,
3572 const MooseVariableBase & ivar,
3573 const MooseVariableBase & jvar,
3574 const std::vector<dof_id_type> & idof_indices,
3575 const std::vector<dof_id_type> & jdof_indices)
3576{
3577 if (idof_indices.size() == 0 || jdof_indices.size() == 0)
3578 return;
3579 if (jac_block.n() == 0 || jac_block.m() == 0)
3580 return;
3581
3582 auto & scaling_factor = ivar.arrayScalingFactor();
3583
3584 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < ivar.count(); ++i)
3585 {
3586 unsigned int iv = ivar.number();
3587 for (const auto & jt : ConstCouplingRow(iv + i, *_cm))
3588 {
3589 unsigned int jv = jvar.number();
3590 if (jt < jv || jt >= jv + jvar.count())
3591 continue;
3592 unsigned int j = jt - jv;
3593
3594 auto di = ivar.componentDofIndices(idof_indices, i);
3595 auto dj = jvar.componentDofIndices(jdof_indices, j);
3596 auto indof = di.size();
3597 auto jndof = dj.size();
3598
3599 unsigned int jj = j;
3600 if (iv == jv && _component_block_diagonal[iv])
3601 // here i must be equal to j
3602 jj = 0;
3603
3604 auto sub = jac_block.sub_matrix(i * indof, indof, jj * jndof, jndof);
3605 if (scaling_factor[i] != 1.0)
3606 sub *= scaling_factor[i];
3607
3608 // If we're computing the jacobian for automatically scaling variables we do not want
3609 // to constrain the element matrix because it introduces 1s on the diagonal for the
3610 // constrained dofs
3611 if (!_sys.computingScalingJacobian())
3612 _dof_map.constrain_element_matrix(sub, di, dj, false);
3613
3614 jacobian.add_matrix(sub, di, dj);
3615 }
3616 }
3617}

3619// private method, so no key required
3620void
3621Assembly::cacheJacobianBlock(DenseMatrix<Number> & jac_block,
3622 const MooseVariableBase & ivar,
3623 const MooseVariableBase & jvar,
3624 const std::vector<dof_id_type> & idof_indices,
3625 const std::vector<dof_id_type> & jdof_indices,
3626 TagID tag)
3627{
3628 if (idof_indices.size() == 0 || jdof_indices.size() == 0)
3629 return;
3630 if (jac_block.n() == 0 || jac_block.m() == 0)
3631 return;
3632 if (!_sys.hasMatrix(tag))
3633 return;
3634
3635 auto & scaling_factor = ivar.arrayScalingFactor();
3636
3637 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < ivar.count(); ++i)
3638 {
3639 unsigned int iv = ivar.number();
3640 for (const auto & jt : ConstCouplingRow(iv + i, *_cm))
3641 {
3642 unsigned int jv = jvar.number();
3643 if (jt < jv || jt >= jv + jvar.count())
3644 continue;
3645 unsigned int j = jt - jv;
3646
3647 auto di = ivar.componentDofIndices(idof_indices, i);
3648 auto dj = jvar.componentDofIndices(jdof_indices, j);
3649 auto indof = di.size();
3650 auto jndof = dj.size();
3651
3652 unsigned int jj = j;
3653 if (iv == jv && _component_block_diagonal[iv])
3654 // here i must be equal to j
3655 jj = 0;
3656
3657 auto sub = jac_block.sub_matrix(i * indof, indof, jj * jndof, jndof);
3658 if (scaling_factor[i] != 1.0)
3659 sub *= scaling_factor[i];
3660
3661 // If we're computing the jacobian for automatically scaling variables we do not want
3662 // to constrain the element matrix because it introduces 1s on the diagonal for the
3663 // constrained dofs
3664 if (!_sys.computingScalingJacobian())
3665 _dof_map.constrain_element_matrix(sub, di, dj, false);
3666
3667 for (MooseIndex(di) i = 0; i < di.size(); i++)
3668 for (MooseIndex(dj) j = 0; j < dj.size(); j++)
3669 {
3670 _cached_jacobian_values[tag].push_back(sub(i, j));
3671 _cached_jacobian_rows[tag].push_back(di[i]);
3672 _cached_jacobian_cols[tag].push_back(dj[j]);
3673 }
3674 }
3675 }
3676
3677 jac_block.zero();
3678}

3681void
3682Assembly::cacheJacobianBlockNonzero(DenseMatrix<Number> & jac_block,
3683 const MooseVariableBase & ivar,
3684 const MooseVariableBase & jvar,
3685 const std::vector<dof_id_type> & idof_indices,
3686 const std::vector<dof_id_type> & jdof_indices,
3687 TagID tag)
3688{
3689 if (idof_indices.size() == 0 || jdof_indices.size() == 0)
3690 return;
3691 if (jac_block.n() == 0 || jac_block.m() == 0)
3692 return;
3693 if (!_sys.hasMatrix(tag))
3694 return;
3695
3696 auto & scaling_factor = ivar.arrayScalingFactor();
3697
3698 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < ivar.count(); ++i)
3699 {
3700 unsigned int iv = ivar.number();
3701 for (const auto & jt : ConstCouplingRow(iv + i, *_cm))
3702 {
3703 unsigned int jv = jvar.number();
3704 if (jt < jv || jt >= jv + jvar.count())
3705 continue;
3706 unsigned int j = jt - jv;

3708 auto di = ivar.componentDofIndices(idof_indices, i);
3709 auto dj = jvar.componentDofIndices(jdof_indices, j);
3710 auto indof = di.size();
3711 auto jndof = dj.size();

3713 unsigned int jj = j;
3714 if (iv == jv && _component_block_diagonal[iv])
3715 // here i must be equal to j
3716 jj = 0;
3717

3719 if (scaling_factor[i] != 1.0)

3721

3730 _cached_jacobian_rows[tag].push_back(di[i]);

3739void
3740Assembly::cacheJacobianBlock(DenseMatrix<Number> & jac_block,
3741 const std::vector<dof_id_type> & idof_indices,
3742 const std::vector<dof_id_type> & jdof_indices,
3743 Real scaling_factor,
3744 LocalDataKey,
3745 TagID tag)
3746{
3747 // Only cache data when the matrix exists
3748 if ((idof_indices.size() > 0) && (jdof_indices.size() > 0) && jac_block.n() && jac_block.m() &&
3749 _sys.hasMatrix(tag))
3750 {
3751 std::vector<dof_id_type> di(idof_indices);
3752 std::vector<dof_id_type> dj(jdof_indices);
3753
3754 // If we're computing the jacobian for automatically scaling variables we do not want to
3755 // constrain the element matrix because it introduces 1s on the diagonal for the constrained
3756 // dofs
3757 if (!_sys.computingScalingJacobian())
3758 _dof_map.constrain_element_matrix(jac_block, di, dj, false);
3759
3760 if (scaling_factor != 1.0)
3761 jac_block *= scaling_factor;
3762
3763 for (MooseIndex(di) i = 0; i < di.size(); i++)
3764 for (MooseIndex(dj) j = 0; j < dj.size(); j++)
3765 {
3766 _cached_jacobian_values[tag].push_back(jac_block(i, j));
3767 _cached_jacobian_rows[tag].push_back(di[i]);
3768 _cached_jacobian_cols[tag].push_back(dj[j]);
3769 }
3770 }
3771 jac_block.zero();
3772}
3773
3774Real
3775Assembly::elementVolume(const Elem * elem) const
3776{
3777 FEType fe_type(elem->default_order(), LAGRANGE);
3778 std::unique_ptr<FEBase> fe(FEBase::build(elem->dim(), fe_type));
3779
3780 // references to the quadrature points and weights
3781 const std::vector<Real> & JxW = fe->get_JxW();
3782 const std::vector<Point> & q_points = fe->get_xyz();
3783
3784 // The default quadrature rule should integrate the mass matrix,
3785 // thus it should be plenty to compute the volume
3786 QGauss qrule(elem->dim(), fe_type.default_quadrature_order());
3787 fe->attach_quadrature_rule(&qrule);
3788 fe->reinit(elem);
3789
3790 // perform a sanity check to ensure that size of quad rule and size of q_points is
3791 // identical
3792 mooseAssert(qrule.n_points() == q_points.size(),
3793 "The number of points in the quadrature rule doesn't match the number of passed-in "
3794 "points in Assembly::setCoordinateTransformation");
3795
3796 // compute the coordinate transformation
3797 Real vol = 0;
3798 for (unsigned int qp = 0; qp < qrule.n_points(); ++qp)
3799 {
3800 Real coord;
3801 coordTransformFactor(_subproblem, elem->subdomain_id(), q_points[qp], coord);
3802 vol += JxW[qp] * coord;
3803 }
3804 return vol;
3805}
3806
3807void
3808Assembly::addCachedJacobian(GlobalDataKey)
3809{
3810 if (!_subproblem.checkNonlocalCouplingRequirement())
3811 {
3812 mooseAssert(_cached_jacobian_rows.size() == _cached_jacobian_cols.size(),
3813 "Error: Cached data sizes MUST be the same!");
3814 for (MooseIndex(_cached_jacobian_rows) i = 0; i < _cached_jacobian_rows.size(); i++)
3815 mooseAssert(_cached_jacobian_rows[i].size() == _cached_jacobian_cols[i].size(),
3816 "Error: Cached data sizes MUST be the same for a given tag!");
3817 }
3818
3819 for (MooseIndex(_cached_jacobian_rows) i = 0; i < _cached_jacobian_rows.size(); i++)
3820 if (_sys.hasMatrix(i))
3821 for (MooseIndex(_cached_jacobian_rows[i]) j = 0; j < _cached_jacobian_rows[i].size(); j++)
3822 _sys.getMatrix(i).add(_cached_jacobian_rows[i][j],
3823 _cached_jacobian_cols[i][j],
3824 _cached_jacobian_values[i][j]);
3825
3826 for (MooseIndex(_cached_jacobian_rows) i = 0; i < _cached_jacobian_rows.size(); i++)
3827 {
3828 if (!_sys.hasMatrix(i))
3829 continue;
3830
3831 if (_max_cached_jacobians < _cached_jacobian_values[i].size())
3832 _max_cached_jacobians = _cached_jacobian_values[i].size();
3833
3834 // Try to be more efficient from now on
3835 // The 2 is just a fudge factor to keep us from having to grow the vector during assembly
3836 _cached_jacobian_values[i].clear();
3837 _cached_jacobian_values[i].reserve(_max_cached_jacobians * 2);
3838
3839 _cached_jacobian_rows[i].clear();
3840 _cached_jacobian_rows[i].reserve(_max_cached_jacobians * 2);
3841
3842 _cached_jacobian_cols[i].clear();
3843 _cached_jacobian_cols[i].reserve(_max_cached_jacobians * 2);
3844 }
3845}

4232
4233void
4234Assembly::addJacobianBlock(SparseMatrix<Number> & jacobian,
4235 unsigned int ivar,
4236 unsigned int jvar,
4237 const DofMap & dof_map,
4238 std::vector<dof_id_type> & dof_indices,
4239 GlobalDataKey,
4240 TagID tag)
4241{
4242 if (dof_indices.size() == 0)
4243 return;
4244 if (!(*_cm)(ivar, jvar))
4245 return;
4246
4247 auto & iv = _sys.getVariable(_tid, ivar);
4248 auto & jv = _sys.getVariable(_tid, jvar);
4249 auto & scaling_factor = iv.arrayScalingFactor();
4250
4251 const unsigned int ivn = iv.number();
4252 const unsigned int jvn = jv.number();
4253 auto & ke = jacobianBlock(ivn, jvn, LocalDataKey{}, tag);
4254
4255 // It is guaranteed by design iv.number <= ivar since iv is obtained
4256 // through SystemBase::getVariable with ivar.
4257 // Most of times ivar will just be equal to iv.number except for array variables,
4258 // where ivar could be a number for a component of an array variable but calling
4259 // getVariable will return the array variable that has the number of the 0th component.
4260 // It is the same for jvar.
4261 const unsigned int i = ivar - ivn;
4262 const unsigned int j = jvar - jvn;
4263
4264 // DoF indices are independently given
4265 auto di = dof_indices;
4266 auto dj = dof_indices;
4267
4268 auto indof = di.size();
4269 auto jndof = dj.size();
4270
4271 unsigned int jj = j;
4272 if (ivar == jvar && _component_block_diagonal[ivn])
4273 jj = 0;
4274
4275 auto sub = ke.sub_matrix(i * indof, indof, jj * jndof, jndof);
4276 // If we're computing the jacobian for automatically scaling variables we do not want to
4277 // constrain the element matrix because it introduces 1s on the diagonal for the constrained
4278 // dofs
4279 if (!_sys.computingScalingJacobian())
4280 dof_map.constrain_element_matrix(sub, di, dj, false);
4281
4282 if (scaling_factor[i] != 1.0)
4283 sub *= scaling_factor[i];
4284
4285 jacobian.add_matrix(sub, di, dj);
4286}

4315 // Most of times ivar will just be equal to iv.number except for array variables,
4316 // where ivar could be a number for a component of an array variable but calling
4317 // getVariable will return the array variable that has the number of the 0th component.
4318 // It is the same for jvar.

4360
4361void
4362Assembly::addJacobianNeighbor(SparseMatrix<Number> & jacobian,
4363 const unsigned int ivar,
4364 const unsigned int jvar,
4365 const DofMap & dof_map,
4366 std::vector<dof_id_type> & dof_indices,
4367 std::vector<dof_id_type> & neighbor_dof_indices,
4368 GlobalDataKey,
4369 const TagID tag)
4370{
4371 if (dof_indices.size() == 0 && neighbor_dof_indices.size() == 0)
4372 return;
4373 if (!(*_cm)(ivar, jvar))
4374 return;
4375
4376 auto & iv = _sys.getVariable(_tid, ivar);
4377 auto & jv = _sys.getVariable(_tid, jvar);
4378 auto & scaling_factor = iv.arrayScalingFactor();
4379
4380 const unsigned int ivn = iv.number();
4381 const unsigned int jvn = jv.number();
4382 auto & ken = jacobianBlockNeighbor(Moose::ElementNeighbor, ivn, jvn, LocalDataKey{}, tag);
4383 auto & kne = jacobianBlockNeighbor(Moose::NeighborElement, ivn, jvn, LocalDataKey{}, tag);
4384 auto & knn = jacobianBlockNeighbor(Moose::NeighborNeighbor, ivn, jvn, LocalDataKey{}, tag);
4385
4386 // It is guaranteed by design iv.number <= ivar since iv is obtained
4387 // through SystemBase::getVariable with ivar.
4388 // Most of times ivar will just be equal to iv.number except for array variables,
4389 // where ivar could be a number for a component of an array variable but calling
4390 // getVariable will return the array variable that has the number of the 0th component.
4391 // It is the same for jvar.
4392 const unsigned int i = ivar - ivn;
4393 const unsigned int j = jvar - jvn;
4394 // DoF indices are independently given
4395 auto dc = dof_indices;
4396 auto dn = neighbor_dof_indices;
4397 auto cndof = dc.size();
4398 auto nndof = dn.size();
4399
4400 unsigned int jj = j;
4401 if (ivar == jvar && _component_block_diagonal[ivn])
4402 jj = 0;
4403
4404 auto suben = ken.sub_matrix(i * cndof, cndof, jj * nndof, nndof);
4405 auto subne = kne.sub_matrix(i * nndof, nndof, jj * cndof, cndof);
4406 auto subnn = knn.sub_matrix(i * nndof, nndof, jj * nndof, nndof);
4407
4408 // If we're computing the jacobian for automatically scaling variables we do not want to
4409 // constrain the element matrix because it introduces 1s on the diagonal for the constrained
4410 // dofs
4411 if (!_sys.computingScalingJacobian())
4412 {
4413 dof_map.constrain_element_matrix(suben, dc, dn, false);
4414 dof_map.constrain_element_matrix(subne, dn, dc, false);
4415 dof_map.constrain_element_matrix(subnn, dn, dn, false);
4416 }
4417
4418 if (scaling_factor[i] != 1.0)
4419 {
4420 suben *= scaling_factor[i];
4421 subne *= scaling_factor[i];
4422 subnn *= scaling_factor[i];
4423 }
4424
4425 jacobian.add_matrix(suben, dc, dn);
4426 jacobian.add_matrix(subne, dn, dc);
4427 jacobian.add_matrix(subnn, dn, dn);
4428}

4443}

4482void
4483Assembly::setCachedJacobian(GlobalDataKey)
4484{
4485 for (MooseIndex(_cached_jacobian_rows) tag = 0; tag < _cached_jacobian_rows.size(); tag++)
4486 if (_sys.hasMatrix(tag))
4487 {
4488 // First zero the rows (including the diagonals) to prepare for
4489 // setting the cached values.
4490 _sys.getMatrix(tag).zero_rows(_cached_jacobian_rows[tag], 0.0);
4491
4492 // TODO: Use SparseMatrix::set_values() for efficiency
4493 for (MooseIndex(_cached_jacobian_values) i = 0; i < _cached_jacobian_values[tag].size(); ++i)
4494 _sys.getMatrix(tag).set(_cached_jacobian_rows[tag][i],
4495 _cached_jacobian_cols[tag][i],
4496 _cached_jacobian_values[tag][i]);
4497 }
4498
4499 clearCachedJacobian();
4500}

4523void
4524Assembly::modifyWeightsDueToXFEM(const Elem * elem)
4525{
4526 mooseAssert(_xfem != nullptr, "This function should not be called if xfem is inactive");
4527
4528 if (_current_qrule == _current_qrule_arbitrary)
4529 return;
4530
4531 MooseArray<Real> xfem_weight_multipliers;
4532 if (_xfem->getXFEMWeights(xfem_weight_multipliers, elem, _current_qrule, _current_q_points))
4533 {
4534 mooseAssert(xfem_weight_multipliers.size() == _current_JxW.size(),
4535 "Size of weight multipliers in xfem doesn't match number of quadrature points");
4536 for (unsigned i = 0; i < xfem_weight_multipliers.size(); i++)
4537 _current_JxW[i] = _current_JxW[i] * xfem_weight_multipliers[i];
4538
4539 xfem_weight_multipliers.release();
4540 }
4541}
4542
4543void
4544Assembly::modifyFaceWeightsDueToXFEM(const Elem * elem, unsigned int side)
4545{
4546 mooseAssert(_xfem != nullptr, "This function should not be called if xfem is inactive");
4547
4548 if (_current_qrule_face == _current_qrule_arbitrary)
4549 return;
4550
4551 MooseArray<Real> xfem_face_weight_multipliers;
4552 if (_xfem->getXFEMFaceWeights(
4553 xfem_face_weight_multipliers, elem, _current_qrule_face, _current_q_points_face, side))
4554 {
4555 mooseAssert(xfem_face_weight_multipliers.size() == _current_JxW_face.size(),
4556 "Size of weight multipliers in xfem doesn't match number of quadrature points");
4557 for (unsigned i = 0; i < xfem_face_weight_multipliers.size(); i++)
4558 _current_JxW_face[i] = _current_JxW_face[i] * xfem_face_weight_multipliers[i];
4559
4560 xfem_face_weight_multipliers.release();
4561 }
4562}

4574 mooseAssert(weights.size() == _current_physical_points.size(), "Size mismatch");

4797void
4798Assembly::helpersRequestData()
4799{
4800 for (unsigned int dim = 0; dim <= _mesh_dimension; dim++)
4801 {
4802 _holder_fe_helper[dim]->get_phi();
4803 _holder_fe_helper[dim]->get_dphi();
4804 _holder_fe_helper[dim]->get_xyz();
4805 _holder_fe_helper[dim]->get_JxW();
4806
4807 _holder_fe_face_helper[dim]->get_phi();
4808 _holder_fe_face_helper[dim]->get_dphi();
4809 _holder_fe_face_helper[dim]->get_xyz();
4810 _holder_fe_face_helper[dim]->get_JxW();
4811 _holder_fe_face_helper[dim]->get_normals();
4812
4813 _holder_fe_face_neighbor_helper[dim]->get_xyz();
4814 _holder_fe_face_neighbor_helper[dim]->get_JxW();
4815 _holder_fe_face_neighbor_helper[dim]->get_normals();
4816
4817 _holder_fe_neighbor_helper[dim]->get_xyz();
4818 _holder_fe_neighbor_helper[dim]->get_JxW();
4819 }
4820
4821 for (unsigned int dim = 0; dim < _mesh_dimension; dim++)
4822 {
4823 // We need these computations in order to compute correct lower-d element volumes in curvilinear
4824 // coordinates
4825 _holder_fe_lower_helper[dim]->get_xyz();
4826 _holder_fe_lower_helper[dim]->get_JxW();
4827 }

4829
4830void
4831Assembly::havePRefinement(const std::vector<FEFamily> & disable_p_refinement_for_families)
4832{
4833 if (_have_p_refinement)
4834 // Already performed tasks for p-refinement
4835 return;
4836
4837 const std::unordered_set<FEFamily> disable_families(disable_p_refinement_for_families.begin(),
4838 disable_p_refinement_for_families.end());
4839
4840 const Order helper_order = _mesh.hasSecondOrderElements() ? SECOND : FIRST;
4841 const FEType helper_type(helper_order, LAGRANGE);
4842 auto process_fe =
4843 [&disable_families](const unsigned int num_dimensionalities, auto & fe_container)
4844 {
4845 if (!disable_families.empty())
4846 for (const auto dim : make_range(num_dimensionalities))
4847 {
4848 auto fe_container_it = fe_container.find(dim);
4849 if (fe_container_it != fe_container.end())
4850 for (auto & [fe_type, fe_ptr] : fe_container_it->second)
4851 if (disable_families.count(fe_type.family))
4852 fe_ptr->add_p_level_in_reinit(false);
4853 }
4854 };
4855 auto process_fe_and_helpers = [process_fe, &helper_type](auto & unique_helper_container,
4856 auto & helper_container,
4857 const unsigned int num_dimensionalities,
4858 const bool user_added_helper_type,
4859 auto & fe_container)
4860 {
4861 unique_helper_container.resize(num_dimensionalities);
4862 for (const auto dim : make_range(num_dimensionalities))
4863 {
4864 auto & unique_helper = unique_helper_container[dim];
4865 unique_helper = FEGenericBase<Real>::build(dim, helper_type);
4866 // don't participate in p-refinement
4867 unique_helper->add_p_level_in_reinit(false);
4868 helper_container[dim] = unique_helper.get();
4869
4870 // If the user did not request the helper type then we should erase it from our FE container
4871 // so that they're not penalized (in the "we should be able to do p-refinement sense") for our
4872 // perhaps silly helpers
4873 if (!user_added_helper_type)
4874 {
4875 auto & fe_container_dim = libmesh_map_find(fe_container, dim);
4876 auto fe_it = fe_container_dim.find(helper_type);
4877 mooseAssert(fe_it != fe_container_dim.end(), "We should have the helper type");
4878 delete fe_it->second;
4879 fe_container_dim.erase(fe_it);
4880 }
4881 }
4882
4883 process_fe(num_dimensionalities, fe_container);
4884 };
4885
4886 // Handle scalar field families
4887 process_fe_and_helpers(_unique_fe_helper,
4888 _holder_fe_helper,
4889 _mesh_dimension + 1,
4890 _user_added_fe_of_helper_type,
4891 _fe);
4892 process_fe_and_helpers(_unique_fe_face_helper,
4893 _holder_fe_face_helper,
4894 _mesh_dimension + 1,
4895 _user_added_fe_face_of_helper_type,
4896 _fe_face);
4897 process_fe_and_helpers(_unique_fe_face_neighbor_helper,
4898 _holder_fe_face_neighbor_helper,
4899 _mesh_dimension + 1,
4900 _user_added_fe_face_neighbor_of_helper_type,
4901 _fe_face_neighbor);
4902 process_fe_and_helpers(_unique_fe_neighbor_helper,
4903 _holder_fe_neighbor_helper,
4904 _mesh_dimension + 1,
4905 _user_added_fe_neighbor_of_helper_type,
4906 _fe_neighbor);
4907 process_fe_and_helpers(_unique_fe_lower_helper,
4908 _holder_fe_lower_helper,
4909 _mesh_dimension,
4910 _user_added_fe_lower_of_helper_type,
4911 _fe_lower);
4912 // Handle vector field families
4913 process_fe(_mesh_dimension + 1, _vector_fe);
4914 process_fe(_mesh_dimension + 1, _vector_fe_face);
4915 process_fe(_mesh_dimension + 1, _vector_fe_neighbor);
4916 process_fe(_mesh_dimension + 1, _vector_fe_face_neighbor);
4917 process_fe(_mesh_dimension, _vector_fe_lower);
4918
4919 helpersRequestData();
4920
4921 _have_p_refinement = true;
4922}
